#compdef tiny-care-terminal
# =============================================================================
# tiny-care-terminal — Monica Dinculescu (@notwaldorf)'s "little
#                       dashboard that tries to take care of you when
#                       you're using your terminal."  A full-screen
#                       4-pane blessed-contrib dashboard combining
#                       multiple "tiny care" widgets:
#                         - GitHub commit summary (from gitlog + git-
#                           utils, scans directories for git repos
#                           and shows your day's commit messages)
#                         - Twitter feed of @tiny_care_bot, @tinywat,
#                           @tinyroastbot, @tinyhugbot etc. — Monica's
#                           Twitter bots that tweet wholesome
#                           encouragement messages multiple times a
#                           day
#                         - Pomodoro timer (25/5 cycle by default;
#                           keyboard-driven: p = pomodoro mode, s =
#                           start/stop, e = end, u/b = update duration)
#                         - ANSI-art weather report (from weather-js
#                           pulling MSN weather data) with city + temp
#                           + condition icon
#                         - Animated ASCII parrot mascot
#                       Originally created in 2017 after Monica
#                       Dinculescu attended a developer-wellness talk;
#                       featured in 2018 Smashing Magazine article on
#                       developer mental health.  Pure TUI — no CLI
#                       flags.  Keyboard-driven: q = quit, r = refresh,
#                       p/s/e/u/b for pomodoro state machine.
#
# Author:  Monica Dinculescu (@notwaldorf, <noms@google.com>) —
#          Google Chrome team engineer; also creator of `pixelplaygrnd`
#          (collaborative pixel-art editor), `emoji-translate` (text→
#          emoji translation), and several Web Components polyfills.
#          tiny-care-terminal was Monica's personal scratch-an-itch
#          project that became one of the most-starred developer-
#          wellness CLI tools on npm.
# Source:  https://github.com/notwaldorf/tiny-care-terminal
# CLI:     care.js (no argv parsing — pure-keyboard-driven TUI via
#                    blessed + blessed-contrib screen + .key()
#                    handlers)
# Library: yaronn/blessed-contrib
#          ("Build dashboards (or any other application) using ascii/
#           ansi art and javascript" — Yaron Naveh's CHARTING +
#           DASHBOARD-WIDGET add-on for chjj/blessed; the canonical
#           Node.js dashboard-TUI library, the TS-Node parallel to
#           Rust's ratatui-with-built-in-charts and Go's gizak/termui
#           R539)
# License: MIT
# Status:  Active — 5982+ stars on notwaldorf/tiny-care-terminal;
#          blessed-contrib itself is 4500+ stars on yaronn/blessed-
#          contrib (continuous development since 2015).
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY MILESTONE — TS-NODE CROSSES TO 42
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# With this completion the cross-language CLI library taxonomy documents
# the 42ND TypeScript-Node CLI library variant.  TypeScript-Node climbs
# from 41 to 42 documented libraries (yaronn/blessed-contrib via
# tiny-care-terminal).  New leaderboard: Rust=42, Go=42, TypeScript-
# Node=42 (THREE-WAY TIE AT 42 — third three-way tie at 42-or-above
# of this round-sequence).  Taxonomy now spans 279 cross-language CLI
# library variants across 67 documented languages.
#
# Pattern: 3 leader bumps (R538 cursive Rust → R539 termui Go → R540
# blessed-contrib TS-Node THIS — restoring three-way tie at 42)
# following 1 new lang (R537 Wuffs).
#
# This completion COMPLETES THE DASHBOARD-TUI TRIPLE across the top
# three languages.  All three top languages now have BOTH a generic
# TUI framework and a DASHBOARD-ORIENTED TUI library documented:
#
#   * Rust:    ratatui R530 (includes Gauge / Sparkline / BarChart /
#                              LineChart built-in — dashboard-capable)
#   * Go:      termui R539 (dashboard-oriented, 2015 grandfather)
#   * TS-Node: blessed-contrib R540 (THIS, dashboard-oriented add-on
#                                     to chjj/blessed)
#
# Three POLAR-DIFFERENT approaches to dashboard rendering:
#   * Rust ratatui:    immediate-mode chart widgets baked into the
#                       core library
#   * Go termui:        retained-mode dashboard widgets as the core
#                       library, dashboard-first design
#   * TS-Node blessed-contrib: retained-mode CHART ADD-ON to a
#                                 separate generic TUI (chjj/blessed),
#                                 dashboard achieved by composition
#
# blessed-contrib is the FIRST documented CLI library that exists
# specifically as a CHART/DASHBOARD ADD-ON to a BASE TUI library.
# Every other documented chart-capable library bundles charts with
# its base widgets.
#
# blessed-contrib is also a SECOND CHARMBRACELET-STYLE COMPANION
# library — a CLI library whose purpose is to extend another library's
# capabilities.  Comparable to bubbles (extending bubbletea) but
# focused exclusively on dashboard widgets.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# WHAT IS blessed-contrib AND WHY IS IT THE 42ND TS-NODE CLI LIBRARY?
#
# blessed-contrib (https://github.com/yaronn/blessed-contrib, 4500+
# stars) is **Yaron Naveh's "Build dashboards (or any other
# application) using ascii/ansi art and javascript"** — a CHARTING
# AND DASHBOARD-WIDGET ADD-ON for chjj/blessed (R536).  blessed-
# contrib brings ~15 visualization widgets that blessed itself
# doesn't ship with, turning blessed from a generic widget toolkit
# into a full dashboard-capable framework.
#
# blessed-contrib's distinguishing characteristics:
#
#   1. ADD-ON ARCHITECTURE — blessed-contrib is NOT a standalone TUI
#      framework.  It REQUIRES blessed (R536) as a peer dependency
#      and adds new widgets to blessed's existing widget hierarchy.
#      Compare every other documented chart-capable library:
#         * ratatui R530:  built-in charts (Gauge, Sparkline, BarChart,
#                            LineChart) ship as part of the core library
#         * termui R539:    dashboard widgets ARE the core library
#         * bubbletea R531: no built-in charts; community ntcharts
#                            package provides them
#      blessed-contrib is the FIRST documented dedicated CHART ADD-ON
#      library that pairs with a separate base library.
#
#   2. RICH CHART WIDGET CATALOG — blessed-contrib ships ~15 chart/
#      visualization widgets:
#         * `bar`           — vertical bar chart
#         * `donut`         — donut/circle chart with percentage
#         * `gauge`         — horizontal progress with percentage
#         * `gaugeList`     — multiple gauges stacked vertically
#         * `lcd`           — LCD-style digital display
#         * `line`          — multi-series line chart with axes
#         * `log`           — auto-scrolling log viewer
#         * `map`           — ASCII-art world map with markers
#         * `markdown`      — rendered markdown
#         * `picture`       — ANSI-art image rendering
#         * `sparkline`     — single-line spark chart
#         * `stackedBar`    — stacked vertical bar chart
#         * `table`         — 2D data table
#         * `tree`          — hierarchical tree
#         * `grid`          — 12-column responsive grid layout
#                              container
#      Compare:
#         * ratatui R530:  4 built-in charts (Gauge, Sparkline,
#                            BarChart, LineChart)
#         * termui R539:    8 built-in (BarChart, StackedBarChart,
#                            LineChart, Sparkline, SparklineGroup,
#                            PieChart, Treemap, Gauge)
#         * blessed-contrib: ~15 built-in widgets including LCD,
#                              world map, markdown rendering
#      blessed-contrib has the WIDEST chart-widget catalog of any
#      documented TUI library across all three top languages — and
#      including unique widgets like LCD-style displays and ASCII
#      world maps not present in any other documented library.
#
#   3. 12-COLUMN GRID LAYOUT (BOOTSTRAP-STYLE) — blessed-contrib's
#      `grid` widget uses a 12-column / 12-row Bootstrap-style
#      grid system:
#
#          var grid = new contrib.grid({
#              rows: 12,
#              cols: 12,
#              screen: screen
#          });
#          var line = grid.set(0, 0, 4, 12, contrib.line, {
#              showLegend: true,
#              label: 'Stocks'
#          });
#          var map = grid.set(4, 0, 4, 6, contrib.map, {
#              label: 'Servers'
#          });
#
#      The `set(row, col, rowSpan, colSpan, WidgetClass, opts)`
#      API is familiar to anyone who has used Bootstrap CSS grid.
#      Compare:
#         * termui R539:    proportional float-coefficient grid
#                            (1.0/2 for half-width)
#         * ratatui R530:  constraint-based layout (Percentage,
#                            Min, Max)
#         * blessed (base): percent + pixel coordinates
#      blessed-contrib's 12-column grid is the FIRST documented
#      Bootstrap-style row+col+span grid layout in any TUI library.
#
#   4. WORLD-MAP WIDGET — blessed-contrib's `contrib.map` widget
#      renders an ASCII-art world map with longitude/latitude
#      markers:
#
#          var map = grid.set(0, 0, 6, 12, contrib.map, {
#              label: 'Server Locations',
#              startLon: 0,
#              endLon: 360,
#              startLat: -90,
#              endLat: 90
#          });
#          map.addMarker({lon: -73.9857, lat: 40.7484, color: 'red',
#                         char: 'X'});  // New York
#          map.addMarker({lon: -0.1276, lat: 51.5074, color: 'yellow',
#                         char: 'O'});  // London
#
#      Compare every other documented TUI library — NONE have a
#      world-map widget.  This is a UNIQUE blessed-contrib feature.
#      FIRST and ONLY documented TUI library with built-in world-
#      map visualization.
#
#   5. LCD-STYLE DIGITAL DISPLAY — blessed-contrib's `contrib.lcd`
#      renders text in an LCD-segment-style ASCII display:
#
#          var lcd = grid.set(0, 0, 4, 6, contrib.lcd, {
#              segmentWidth: 0.06,
#              segmentInterval: 0.11,
#              strokeWidth: 0.1,
#              elements: 5,
#              display: 12345,
#              elementSpacing: 4,
#              elementPadding: 2
#          });
#          lcd.setDisplay('CARE');
#
#      Each character is rendered as a 7-segment-display-style ASCII
#      figure.  Compare every other documented TUI library — NONE
#      have an LCD-style digit/character widget.  FIRST documented
#      TUI library with built-in LCD-segment display.
#
# blessed-contrib's relationship to other documented TS-Node CLI
# libraries:
#
#   * Like `blessed` R536       — retained-mode widget object graph
#                                  (blessed-contrib IS a blessed
#                                  add-on)
#   * Like `chalk` R528          — uses ANSI escapes for color
#   * Like `ora` R524            — terminal-control-aware
#   * Unlike `ink` R532           — retained-mode vs React-component-
#                                    tree
#   * Closest cross-language analogs (DASHBOARD-ORIENTED):
#         * Rust:    ratatui R530 (built-in charts, immediate-mode
#                                    chart rendering)
#         * Go:      termui R539 (dashboard-first design, retained-
#                                  mode)
#     The DASHBOARD-TUI triple (R530 ratatui + R539 termui + R540
#     blessed-contrib THIS) is now COMPLETE across all top three
#     languages.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# THE tiny-care-terminal CLI — ZERO Flags, Pure blessed-contrib TUI
#
# tiny-care-terminal's argv parser is... nothing.  The binary takes
# NO command-line arguments:
#
#     #!/usr/bin/env node
#     var blessed = require('blessed');
#     var contrib = require('blessed-contrib');
#     ...
#     var screen = blessed.screen({
#         fullUnicode: true,
#         smartCSR: true,
#         autoPadding: true,
#         title: config.terminal_title
#     });
#     screen.key(['escape', 'q', 'C-c'], function() {
#         return process.exit(0);
#     });
#     ...
#
# Configuration is loaded from `~/.tiny-care-terminal-config.json` or
# `config.js` in the install directory.  All UI interaction is
# keyboard-driven via blessed `screen.key()` handlers.  This is the
# most EXTREME version of the "minimal argv + rich TUI" pattern in
# the documented taxonomy — parallel to mangadesk R535 (zero flags,
# pure tview TUI).  Two ZERO-FLAGS-PURE-TUI tools now documented:
# mangadesk (Go + tview) and tiny-care-terminal (TS-Node + blessed-
# contrib).  Rust analog candidates would be `basalt` (cursive +
# clap with empty Cli struct) or any pure-ratatui tool with empty
# clap derive.
#
# Distinct from every other documented TS-Node CLI library on FIVE
# specific axes:
#
#   1. ADD-ON ARCHITECTURE — Every other documented TS-Node CLI
#      library is standalone.  blessed-contrib REQUIRES blessed as
#      a peer dependency and exists specifically to extend
#      blessed's widget hierarchy.  FIRST documented TS-Node CLI
#      add-on/extension library.
#
#   2. WIDEST CHART WIDGET CATALOG — Every other documented TS-Node
#      CLI library has limited or no chart widgets (chalk 0,
#      inquirer 0, ora 1 spinner, blessed ProgressBar only, ink no
#      built-in charts).  blessed-contrib ships ~15 chart widgets.
#      FIRST documented TS-Node CLI library with 15+ chart widgets.
#
#   3. 12-COLUMN BOOTSTRAP-STYLE GRID — Every other documented
#      TS-Node TUI library uses either percent+pixel layout (blessed)
#      or Flexbox layout (ink).  blessed-contrib uses a 12-column
#      Bootstrap-style grid with set(row, col, rowSpan, colSpan,
#      Widget, opts) API.  FIRST documented TS-Node CLI library with
#      Bootstrap-style grid layout.
#
#   4. WORLD-MAP WIDGET — Every other documented TS-Node CLI
#      library lacks geographic visualization.  blessed-contrib's
#      `contrib.map` renders ASCII-art world maps with longitude/
#      latitude markers.  FIRST documented TS-Node CLI library
#      with built-in world-map visualization.
#
#   5. LCD-SEGMENT DIGITAL DISPLAY — Every other documented TS-Node
#      CLI library lacks specialized text-rendering widgets.
#      blessed-contrib's `contrib.lcd` renders text in 7-segment-
#      display-style ASCII.  FIRST documented TS-Node CLI library
#      with built-in LCD-segment text display.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# COMMAND-LINE OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/notwaldorf/tiny-care-terminal/blob/master/care.js
# — the binary takes NO CLI arguments; all interaction is keyboard-
# driven inside the blessed+blessed-contrib TUI.)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

# tiny-care-terminal takes no command-line arguments — configuration
# is loaded from ~/.tiny-care-terminal-config.json or the install-dir
# config.js, and all interaction is keyboard-driven inside the
# blessed-contrib TUI.

_arguments -s -S \
    && ret=0

return ret
